parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake calipers can cause the brakes to drag excessively, leading to overheating of the hubcaps, and potentially resulting in complete brake failure, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brakes drag excessively
the hubcaps overheat
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the master cylinder level is low
the brake fluid level is low
the rubber diaphragm under the cap is expanded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake sensor can cause the brake sensor light to stay on, indicating a potential brake problem, which can lead to accidents or loss of control if not addressed.
symptoms: The brake sensor light stays on
the brake system warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A gas tank leak can cause fuel to spill on the road, leading to a fire hazard, accidents, or environmental damage.
symptoms: Fuel pouring from the rear of the tank when filling up at a station.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose or fallen sway bar bolts can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Bolts fell from the vehicle while driving
causing the sway bar to malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A deflated airbag in the suspension system can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Right front airbag in the suspension system deflated after only 49 days of use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective differential can cause fluid to leak from the axle tube, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Fluid leaking from the axle tube in the rear-end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A mangled or twisted shock bracket can cause the shock to fall, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Shock bracket mangled and twisted
causing the shock to fall.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dash Air and Cooling System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning dash air and cooling system can cause overheating, leaks, and discomfort for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Dash air blows hot air when sitting in traffic or at idle
overheats
and leaks antifreeze.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive vibration and poor handling can cause fatigue, loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Extreme vibration felt in the steering wheel
floor
and dashboard
making it hard to read gauges; excessive sway in turns and when passing other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Microwave Oven with Unattended Startup
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The microwave oven can start operating on its own without user input, posing a fire hazard and risk of injury or property damage.
symptoms: The microwave oven turns on by itself
without being initiated by the user
and can potentially cause a fire or other safety issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric park brake system can cause the vehicle to become disabled, leading to safety risks and inconvenience, as well as potential damage to surrounding property.
symptoms: The park brake system becomes disabled
hydraulic fluid leaks from the system
the vehicle requires towing for repair
the sensor
actuator
switch
and pump fail and need to be replaced.
